{
  "text": "EpCAM is an epithelial cell adhesion molecule, which based on its capability to mediate cell-cell adhesions, has been classified to the broad family of cell adhesion molecules (CAMs). However, EpCAM is an atypical cell adhesion molecule that, based on its structure, cannot be grouped in the known cell adhesion family groups of cadherins, selectins, integrins and immunoglobulin superfamily [CITATION_1] .",
